# Architecture Rules

## Layering
```
UI/Controller → Application/Use Case → Domain → Infrastructure
```
- Each layer depends ONLY on the one below, via interfaces.
- Domain knows nothing about DB, HTTP, framework.

## Module boundaries
- Public API explicit (`index.ts`, `__init__.py`).
- NO circular dependencies.

## Dependency Injection
- Inject via constructor / params; DO NOT `new` infrastructure inside domain.

## Side effects
- I/O, network, time, randomness at the edges.
- Domain logic pure when possible.

## Configuration
- From env vars; validate at startup; fail fast.

## Logging & observability
- Correlation ID end-to-end.
- Log entry/exit of use cases + on errors.
- Metrics on every external call.

## Violations to flag 🟠+
- Domain importing HTTP / SQL / framework.
- Fat controller with complex business logic.
- Mutable global state via singletons.
